## § 9 — Retweet (Batch from Feed)

Retweet multiple tweets from the feed in a SINGLE evaluate. No per-tweet navigation needed.
Pass `targetUrls` as an array of href paths (e.g. `['/user/status/123', ...]`).

```javascript
// On home feed page — batch retweet with Promise chain
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    const targetUrls = ${JSON.stringify(targetUrls)};
    const tweets = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('article[data-testid="tweet"]'));
    const results = [];

    function rtOne(idx) {
      return new Promise(resolve => {
        if (idx >= targetUrls.length) { resolve(); return; }
        const url = targetUrls[idx];
        const target = tweets.find(t => {
          const link = t.querySelector('a[href*="/status/"]');
          return link && link.getAttribute('href') === url;
        });
        if (!target) { results.push({ url, error: 'not found' }); resolve(rtOne(idx + 1)); return; }
        const btn = target.querySelector('[data-testid="retweet"]');
        if (!btn) { results.push({ url, already: !!target.querySelector('[data-testid="unretweet"]') }); resolve(rtOne(idx + 1)); return; }
        btn.click();
        setTimeout(() => {
          const items = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[role="menuitem"]'));
          const repostBtn = items.find(i => i.innerText.includes('Repost'));
          if (!repostBtn) { results.push({ url, error: 'no repost option' }); resolve(rtOne(idx + 1)); return; }
          repostBtn.click();
          setTimeout(() => {
            const ok = !!target.querySelector('[data-testid="unretweet"]');
            results.push({ url, retweeted: ok });
            resolve(rtOne(idx + 1));
          }, 1500);
        }, 1000);
      });
    }

    return rtOne(0).then(() => ({ results, count: results.filter(r => r.retweeted).length }));
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

Returns `{ results: [...], count: N }`. Each result has `url` + `retweeted: true/false`.
🚨 Do NOT navigate to individual tweets for retweeting — batch from feed is 1 step instead of 21.

## § 10 — Thread (Hook-then-Reply)

🚨 **NEVER use the multi-textarea thread composer** — snapshot de-dupes same aria-label so you can't type into the second slot. The hook-then-reply approach is the ONLY supported thread method.

### Pattern: post hook → navigate to it → reply sequentially

**Step 1 — Post hook tweet via compose dialog (§ 7 pattern):**
```
navigate("https://x.com/home")
evaluate → click compose button
snapshot('[role="dialog"] [data-testid="tweetTextarea_0"]') → type hook text → snapshot('[role="dialog"] [data-testid="tweetButton"]') → click
🚨 MUST use dialog-scoped selectors — see BROWSER-core.md § 1
```

**Step 2 — Get hook tweet URL from profile:**
```javascript
// Navigate to profile, extract latest tweet URL
browser.navigate("https://x.com/{{handle_slug}}", { profile: "{{browser_profile}}" })
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(() => {
      const articles = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('article[data-testid="tweet"]'));
      const first = articles[0];
      if (!first) return resolve({ error: 'no tweets' });
      const link = first.querySelector('a[href*="/status/"]');
      const text = first.querySelector('[data-testid="tweetText"]')?.innerText?.slice(0, 80) || '';
      resolve({ url: link ? 'https://x.com' + link.getAttribute('href') : '', text });
    }, 2000));
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

**Step 3 — Reply chain (repeat for each body tweet + CTA):**
```
navigate(hookTweetUrl)
snapshot([data-testid="tweetTextarea_0"]) → ref=eN
type(eN, tweetText)
snapshot([data-testid="tweetButtonInline"]) → ref=eM
click(eM)
verify: evaluate → check articles contain @{{handle_slug}} reply
```

For tweet 3+: navigate to the PREVIOUS reply URL (not the hook), so the chain stays linear.
Get each reply URL after posting:
```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(() => {
      const articles = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('article[data-testid="tweet"]'));
      const ours = articles.filter(a => {
        const h = a.querySelector('[data-testid="User-Name"]')?.innerText?.split('\\n').find(l => l.startsWith('@'));
        return h === '@{{handle_slug}}';
      });
      const latest = ours[ours.length - 1];
      const link = latest?.querySelector('a[href*="/status/"]');
      resolve({
        count: ours.length,
        latestUrl: link ? 'https://x.com' + link.getAttribute('href') : ''
      });
    }, 1500));
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

### Cost: ~18 steps for 5-tweet thread (~$1.00) vs 68 steps with broken composer (~$9.00).

